2.5 Customizing the colors
I have prepared a style file at html/styles.scss, which contains the core configuration from the fabulous website of Andrew Heiss. This section defines the colors of the website which are used throughout many pages.


html/styles.scss

$primary:   $teal!default;
$secondary: $gray-700 !default;
$success:   $green !default;
$info:      $cyan !default;
$warning:   $orange !default;
$danger:    $red !default;
$light:     $gray-400 !default;
$dark:      $black !default;

The most important field is arguably $primary. If you want your website to look mainly green, just change that line to $primary: $green!default;. Note that $teal and $green are SCSS variables, which are defined further up in the file. If you want to fine-tune your color palette, you can change these HEX codes.
